key":"zmzkhQuA5o"}],"key":"rg4o4OgAFk"}],"key":"N6U2O24Su5"},{"type":"block","position":{"start":{"line":133,"column":1},"end":{"line":133,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":135,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Multiprocess the generator","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":135,"column":1}},"key":"aImCBwnimv"}],"identifier":"multiprocess-the-generator","label":"Multiprocess the generator","html_id":"multiprocess-the-generator","implicit":true,"key":"QIZYHuIjnT"}],"key":"shUM1OutjZ"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"# Both input and output are a list of file strings\ndef multi_generate(fstrs, procs=None):\n    pool = multiprocessing.Pool(\n        procs\n    )  # Pool of processors. Defaults to all available logical cores\n\n    results = []\n    # chunksize=1 means feed a process a new job as soon as the process is idle.\n    # In our case, this restricts the queue to one \"dispatcher\" which is faster.\n    r = pool.map_async(generate, fstrs, chunksize=1, callback=results.append)\n    r.wait()\n\n    return results[0]","key":"F2Kt6dwKsa"},{"type":"outputs","id":"5A4QEI2B1S72HM6xN6IOy","children":[],"key":"o7w9HPvhCa"}],"key":"nKID9163vv"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":153,"column":1},"end":{"line":153,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Feed the monster, asynchronously!","position":{"start":{"line":153,"column":1},"end":{"line":153,"column":1}},"key":"rFWY0dqOtg"}],"identifier":"feed-the-monster-asynchronously","label":"Feed the monster, asynchronously!","html_id":"feed-the-monster-asynchronously","implicit":true,"key":"rdsarUy8s4"}],"key":"d22BKcWXoU"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"before = time.time()\nofstrs = multi_generate(ifstrs)\nafter = time.time()\n\nprint(\"Processing time: %3.2f seconds\" % (after - before))","key":"e2t3Xk25fa"},{"type":"outputs","id":"d8S216ndwtxYYbG2SbWTY","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":"Processing time: 2.43 seconds\n"},"key":"CTlWM79aZe"}],"key":"Fgze41BP2R"}],"key":"nJNpQTOvfQ"},{"type":"block","children":[],"key":"BdpXbObkna"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"","key":"PWSGveq3AH"},{"type":"outputs","id":"2xlU5FWG5ofvuWZH8WVWl","children":[],"key":"q7KiMuvYCj"}],"key":"xViaqwQJCO"}],"key":"BLcw3EGQSx"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Quality Control using DR","url":"/notebooks/baltrad/baltrad-short-course/baltrad-drqc","group":"BALTRAD"},"next":{"title":"Compositing","url":"/notebooks/baltrad/baltrad-short-course/baltrad-compositing","group":"BALTRAD"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}